--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, &quot;babiarz3&quot; &lt;babiarz3@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; Time is absolutely being removed from the audio files. There is so
&gt; much more than just listening to the files, you have too look. You
&gt; have to train your eyes as well as your ears to make any sort of
&gt; judgment. The second I load some of these files, before I listen, I
&gt; see problems. I know the site isn&#39;t set up to really leave comments 
on
&gt; files with the file but something should be included in the name or
&gt; something. Without it, it is not true representation of what the 
file
&gt; is or what has happened between the capture and the post. We listen
&gt; and think &quot;Wow! Great catch&quot; but we really do not know. 
&gt; 
&gt; Are you starting the scan on your 3 469&#39;s at different frequencies?
&gt; What is the ratio being mixed? Is it equal between the three? 
&gt; 
&gt; I believe that Mark and Debbie Constantino (sp)of Nevada use water
&gt; almost exclusively for their recordings. I have found that method to
&gt; be difficult in hearing the results. Are you feeling that those
&gt; communications are from spirits or earthbounds and what makes you 
feel
&gt; that way?
&gt; 
&gt; I&#39;ve recently started analyzing a 40 min 469 session. The results 
are
&gt; scary. I&#39;d say at this point, and I&#39;m only 1/2 way through, 90% of 
the
&gt; communication is negative in nature and mentions many supposed 
Demonic
&gt; names. The layers of voices are, in many cases, multiple. Often, the
&gt; listener hears very little of what is actually said. The voices can 
be
&gt; mocking or downright crude. I have not yet formed an opinion fully 
but
&gt; it would seem to me that these models are easy devices for lower 
level
&gt; entities to figure out how to use. I can not speak of the attitudes 
or
&gt; fears of those investigators present although at times, their voices
&gt; are a bit shaky. 
&gt; 
&gt; Babs
&gt; 
&gt; --- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, Frank Ratka &lt;warrior18eii@&gt; wrote:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Very good observation Babs. Let me say that you have many friends
&gt; and associates here just for the simple fact that you have an 
interest
&gt; in ITC, are a researcher and a complex thinker. I think we have 
shown
&gt; in the past that we can have a disagreement and still remain 
friends.
&gt; You make a lot of good points in your post and I would like to know
&gt; who removes time from their recordings. I have never removed time 
from
&gt; my recordings and see no reason why anyone else would without saying
&gt; so in an accompanied post.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; I have limited experience with the 12-469&#39;s as a single piece of
&gt; equipment. I have arranged mine per Mike&#39;s, &quot;Spiricomp&quot; design. I 
have
&gt; 3, 12-469&#39;s feeding a four channel mixer, which goes into a laptop
&gt; running DC6 with Soundsoap 2. Mine scan equally spaced on the FM 
band.
&gt; I have had pretty good results until recently.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; At first the messages were pretty clear but I had a feeling I was
&gt; getting a different group than I normally have for the last few 
years.
&gt; When I would ask about my friends on the other side they would tell 
me
&gt; they will look for them. Well about 2 weeks ago the 12-469 
arrangement
&gt; started generating a lot of interference and feedback. I started
&gt; hearing radio static voices as I use to get with shortwave. Not 
voice
&gt; fragments but voices made of static (metallic and robotic). They 
were
&gt; breaking through the sweeping. I had a feeling someone else was 
trying
&gt; to force their way through. Finally the interference got so bad I 
was
&gt; forced to revert back to a simpler method I used before, which is
&gt; using fan noise. One of the first messages to come across was from a
&gt; familiar voice telling me and I quote, &quot;your method sucks&quot;. I have 
not
&gt; used the 12-469&#39;s since because of the clear messages I have been
&gt; getting using water and fan noise. That does not mean I have given 
up
&gt; &gt;  on the 12-469&#39;s but I won&#39;t use them again until I am persuaded 
to
&gt; by my friends on the otherside that they are willing to use and 
adapt
&gt; to it. To my knowledge only Misty, Laura and myself use water for
&gt; recording.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; Regards,
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; Frank R.
