&gt; &gt;             Alright, you all know I&#39;m vocal and I haven&#39;t made any
&gt; &quot;friends&quot; here
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; but, if we can put that aside for a moment...
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; Spirit communication has been my passion since day one, a little 
over
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; 6 years ago. I am a believer in the afterlife and a believer in
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; spirits attempting to communicate with us for a variety of 
reasons. I
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; have spiritual beliefs that I feel strongly about and devote much 
of
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; my waking (and sleeping) moments to thoughts about this field.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; However, I am also a researcher and a skeptic. In order for me to
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; allow ideas to become part of my reality I must experiment. In 
order
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; for me to believe something is paranormal I HAVE to rule out all 
other
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; possible causes. That being said, I have some questions. My hope 
is
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; that there are some here willing to enter into discussion with me.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; I have a difficult time with many of the files here. Many times, 
there
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; is no question included in the file. I can not determine whether 
or
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; not the &quot;reply&quot; is an intelligent reply. Maybe this has to do with
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; allowable file size.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; Some of the files I have been able to download. (I don&#39;t always 
keep
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; my email settings on for this group as I get too many - lol) When 
I
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; look at the file I see problems. There will be complete flat line
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; silence between the words. Many times the &quot;reply&quot; is also at the 
same
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; decibel as the question askers voice. Those two things should not
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; occur naturally considering the devices being used. That tells me 
that
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; there is manipulation of the files. Now, what is manipulation to 
me,
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; may not be manipulation to others. To me, any altering of the 
recorded
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; file constitutes manipulation. I do not know if the reply was
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; intelligent or manipulated to be intelligent. 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; Some say that they simply remove the &quot;no response&quot; time. I&#39;ve been
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; told it can be as much as 18 seconds removed from between words. 
Now
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; we run into the problem of us deciding what word fits in with the
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; question. What words are being ignored?  Did we take nonsense and 
make
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; sense? Did we amp every noise/word or only what fit?
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; I think it&#39;s great that files are offered for peer review. 
However, I
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; think we have to load them untouched or at the very least, offer
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; exactly what was done to the entire file. Time elapsed between 
words,
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; what was amped, etc. I&#39;d also love to see some of these sessions 
video
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; taped with the question asker facing the camera and a second hand
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; clock visible. Truly, we aren&#39;t researching if we don&#39;t have some
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; protocol in place.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; Here is an issue I have with the RS Hacks. I have the 469. It 
takes
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; approximately 18 seconds to scan through the AM frequencies. Now, 
the
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; typical person would think that we can take that 18 seconds and 
divide
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; it by the number of AM stations to determine how long we are on 
each
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; station before moving on to the next one. In that way we could
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; determine what is impossible to be said via a radio fragment. 
However,
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; that&#39;s not correct. The scan cycle can vary from one frequency to 
the
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; next and of course the biggest problem is that some stations are
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; picked up over multiple frequencies; AM 640 can be heard on 630, 
640,
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; 650, 660 and maybe even 670. That extends the time a great deal. 
This
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; is a difficult problem because it is almost impossible for the 
average
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; person to be able to make a determination on time this way. 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; I heard about the following today; An experimenter records at the 
same
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; time every day Mon-Fri. We hear about the importance of 
meditating,
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; automatic writing, etc at the same time every day but what we 
have to
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; remember with this, is that now we are in essence tuning into the 
same
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; radio show every day. One of my first experiments with the 469 
had me
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; hearing this deep male voice over and over again. What was he 
trying
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; to tell me, I wondered. Than I realized that he was speaking
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; approximately every 18 seconds; every time the scan hit that 
station.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; So, if you are removing up to 18 seconds between words, then you 
are
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; really only recording the words from one station. 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; This post is IN NO WAY trying to start anything besides discussion
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; about some research problems. I know that there are those who are 
not
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; concerned with anything more than the communication itself but I 
think
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; that it is of the utmost importance to attempt to factor in some
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; protocol in order for this to be considered serious research at 
all. 
